race.comment: GOLDEN SUNSET (14) came from this same handicap when winning heats of this series in her last two outings at this circuit. Scored by 4m over this distance in round one, taking her strike rate at the journey to 50 per cent. She is a reliable mare who hasn't missed the top three this time in. Can land the hat trick. HIDE AND SEEK (15) worked to the front from this mark before scoring a 1.5m win in his latest heat. His strike rate at this longer distance also stands at 50 per cent so he looks a danger. ZEALOUS SPUR NZ (13) has 6m to make up on GOLDEN SUNSET through the last-start third but he dug deep to win in round one so should enjoy getting back out over longer journey. GET USED TO IT (10) hasn't won for a while but is consistent, adding to a long string of top-four finishes by placings in both rounds of the series.
